data.name: Beef Tenderloin Stir-Fry
data.quickTastyDescription: A quick, savory stir-fry featuring tender beef and vibrant vegetables, perfect for a weeknight dinner.
detailedCookingInstructions: Slice the beef tenderloin into thin strips against the grain.
In a large skillet or wok, heat the vegetable oil over medium-high heat.
Add the garlic and ginger, saut√©ing for about 30 seconds until fragrant.
Add the sliced beef to the skillet, cooking for about 5 minutes until browned.
Stir in the bell peppers and broccoli, cooking for an additional 4-5 minutes until the vegetables are tender but still crisp.
Pour in the soy sauce, stir well to combine, and season with salt and black pepper to taste.
Serve hot over rice or noodles.
